---
title: Roasted Cauliflower Flatbreads Serves as a Holiday Side Dish or a Regular Main
description: This is essentially a pizza with tricked-out, Mediterranean-style toppings that would make any traditionalist scratch their head. But forget tradition, we say, because it’s pretty darn tasty. With warm cauliflower, caramelized onion, and a drizzle of honey tahini, it brings together savory and sweet flavors unlike anything else you’ve likely ever experienced. And even better, it works brilliantly as an appetizer for a crowd when cut into bite-size pieces (hey there, Thanksgiving), but it’s also a fantastic meal for two any night of the week.
